    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/1926</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Messrs. <persName type="from">Shearman &amp;
                            Sterling</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1927</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: We are informed that there is shortly to be
                    submitted to you by the Republic of Liberia an executed counterpart of a Loan
                    Agreement, dated September 1, 1926, between the Republic of Liberia, the Finance
                    Corporation of America, and The National City Bank of New York, as Fiscal Agent,
                    with the request to be informed whether the Department of State of the United
                    States will undertake the obligations imposed upon it by this Agreement.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d143fn2">For text of the agreement, see <ref
                            target="frus1926v02#pg_574">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 574</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In the event that your reply is in the affirmative, the Finance Corporation of
                    America and the Fiscal Agent, as the other two parties to the Agreement, will
                    greatly appreciate being so informed by you.</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shearman &amp; Sterling</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Attorneys for Finance Corporation of America and<lb/>The
                        National City Bank of New York as Fiscal Agent</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
